Step 1: Identify the necessary values.
• From the cash flow statement, the net cash flow from operating activities is –7,724,112.71.
• From the balance sheet, the “Total Current Liabilities” is 737,762.05. (In this problem there are no other liabilities shown, so we consider total liabilities equal to current liabilities.)

Step 2: Compute the Cash Flow to Debt Ratio using the formula:
  Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Total Debt)
  = (–7,724,112.71) / (737,762.05)

Step 3: Do the division:
  –7,724,112.71 ÷ 737,762.05 ≈ –10.47

Step 4: Present the answer.

{
  "solution": {
    "Cash Flow to Debt Ratio": "-10.47"
  }
}
